# YouTube Focus Extension

Chrome extension (Manifest V3) that blocks YouTube Shorts and entertainment content to help users stay focused on educational videos.

## Tech Stack

- **Manifest V3** — Chrome extension platform
- **TypeScript** — all source code
- **Vite** + **@crxjs/vite-plugin** — build tooling with HMR
- **Vanilla TS + CSS** — no UI framework (popup and content scripts)
- **Chrome Storage API (sync)** — persisted user settings

## Core Features

1. **Shorts blocking** — blur Shorts with overlay + icon, across all YouTube surfaces (homepage, sidebar, Shorts shelf, Shorts page)
2. **Category filtering** — block videos by YouTube category (Gaming, Entertainment, etc. — NOT Music)
3. **Keyword filtering** — user-defined blocklist matched against titles/descriptions
4. **Channel filtering** — user-defined allow/block lists per channel
5. **Simple popup** — on/off toggle + quick access to filter settings

## Project Structure

```
src/
  background/
    service-worker.ts     # Background service worker
  content/
    index.ts              # Content script entry
    observers.ts          # MutationObservers for SPA navigation
    filters/
      shorts.ts           # Shorts detection and blurring
      categories.ts       # Category-based filtering
      keywords.ts         # Keyword-based filtering
      channels.ts         # Channel-based filtering
    ui/
      overlay.ts          # Blur overlay component
      styles.css          # Injected styles
  popup/
    index.html
    popup.ts
    popup.css
  shared/
    types.ts              # Shared TypeScript types
    storage.ts            # Chrome Storage wrapper
    constants.ts          # Default blocked categories, selectors
  manifest.json
```

## Architecture Notes

- Content scripts use `MutationObserver` to handle YouTube's SPA navigation
- Category detection parses `ytInitialData` / meta tags from the page (no API key required)
- All filtering runs client-side in the content script
- Background service worker handles storage events and cross-tab state
- Scheduling support is planned for later (not MVP)
